com.inrix.sdk.model

Class TripPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrix.sdk.model.TripPoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable, Cloneable

    public class TripPoint
extends Object
implements Parcelable, Cloneable
    Represents any location associated with a Trip, including the origin, destination, or any intermediate way-points on the Trip.

    There are two ways to reference a location when creating a TripPoint:

    • Using a Location from the user's saved locations
    • Using a GeoPoint with latitude/longitude coordinates

    Additional details (beyond the coordinates and the name) about the TripPoint can be retrieved using the LocationsManager if the TripPoint references a Location.

    NOTE: Any name specified during creation will not be modified based on current language or locale settings. Calling TripPoint.getName() always returns the value which was provided when creating the TripPoint instance.

      • getName

        public String getName()
        Get the name of this location.

        If there was no name provided when the TripPoint was created then this method will return null. In this case the GeoPoint should be converted into a user-friendly location to obtain a user-friendly location using a reverse geocode.

        Returns:
        name of the location

      • getDuration

        public int getDuration()
        Get the duration (in minutes) the user will stop at this location. This value is only relevant if the TripPoint is one of the way-points on a Trip and will be ignored if the TripPoint is the origin or destination.
        Returns:
        duration (in minutes)

      • setDuration

        public void setDuration(int duration)
        Set the duration (in minutes) the user will stop at this location. This value is only relevant if the TripPoint is one of the way-points on a Trip and will be ignored if the TripPoint is the origin or destination.

        The duration must also be a non-negative value, and negative values are ignored and the duration defaults to 0.

        Parameters:
        duration - duration (in minutes)

      • isDeleted

        public boolean isDeleted()
        Returns true if the Location used to create this TripPoint has been deleted.

        If true, this implies that the TripPoint.getLocationId() is no longer valid.

        Returns:
        true if the associated Location has been deleted, false otherwise or if the TripPoint was not created from a Location

      • getTimeZone

        public TimeZone getTimeZone()
        Returns the TimeZone for this TripPoint. The time zone can be used to calculate a meaningful arrival/departure time for a Trip given travel time.

        The timezone is only available after the Trip has been saved.

        Returns:
        time zone at this TripPoint, or null if the time zone is not available
